{
  "category": "Uncategorized",
  "description": "# Gmail Email Ingestion via Google Pub/Sub & Apps Script\n\nHere's the full spec rewritten for Gmail, using **Google Pub/Sub push subscriptions** (Gmail's native webhook mechanism) as the backbone instead of Power Automate.\n\n---\n\n## How Gmail \"Webhooks\" Actually Work\n\nGmail doesn't support direct webhooks, but Google provides an official push notification system:\n\n1. **Gmail Watch API** ‚Äî tells Gmail to monitor an inbox and publish notifications to a Google Pub/Sub topic when new messages arrive\n2. **Google Pub/Sub** ‚Äî receives those notifications and immediately pushes them to your HTTPS endpoint\n3. **Your backend** ‚Äî receives the Pub/Sub push, uses the Gmail API to fetch the actual email content, and ingests it\n\nThis is the production-grade approach used by enterprise Gmail integrations. Alternatively, for tenants who prefer a no-code setup, **Google Apps Script** can poll Gmail and POST to your webhook on a time trigger ‚Äî this is simpler but introduces up to a 1-minute delay.\n\n---\n\n## Webhook Endpoint\n\n**Primary endpoint (Pub/Sub push):**\n```\nPOST /webhooks/email/gmail/:tenantId\n```\n\n**Authentication:** Pub/Sub push requests include a Bearer token in the `Authorization` header issued by Google. Verify this token against Google's token info endpoint (`https://oauth2.googleapis.com/tokeninfo`) to confirm it's a legitimate Pub/Sub push and that the `email` claim matches your registered service account. Additionally, validate a `?token=<secret>` query parameter appended to the subscription push URL during setup as a secondary layer.\n\n**What Pub/Sub delivers:** The push payload is a Pub/Sub message envelope ‚Äî not the email itself. The `data` field is base64-encoded and contains only the Gmail `historyId` and the user's email address. Your backend must then call the Gmail API to retrieve the actual message.\n\n**Ingestion flow:**\n\n```\nPub/Sub Push ‚Üí Your endpoint ‚Üí Decode historyId ‚Üí Gmail API (history.list) \n‚Üí Gmail API (messages.get) ‚Üí Parse & store email\n```\n\n**Parse and extract from Gmail API response:**\n- `from` header ‚Üí sender address\n- `to`, `cc`, `bcc` headers ‚Üí recipients\n- `subject` header ‚Üí subject\n- `body.data` (text/plain part) ‚Üí plain text body\n- `body.data` (text/html part) ‚Üí HTML body\n- `internalDate` ‚Üí received timestamp\n- `id` ‚Üí Gmail message ID (used for deduplication)\n- `threadId` ‚Üí conversation thread reference\n- `payload.parts` where `filename` is non-empty ‚Üí attachment metadata (name, MIME type, size, attachment ID)\n\n**HTTP responses:**\n- `200` ‚Äî success or duplicate (Pub/Sub will not retry on 200)\n- `400` ‚Äî payload malformed or tenant resolution failed\n- `401` ‚Äî auth token invalid\n- `500` ‚Äî internal error (Pub/Sub **will** retry, so only use this when a retry is appropriate)\n\n> **Critical:** Return `200` for duplicates and known-bad messages you've already handled. Returning non-2xx causes Pub/Sub to retry with exponential backoff for up to 7 days.\n\n---\n\n## Database\n\n```sql\nCREATE TABLE emails (\n  id                UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),\n  tenant_id         UUID NOT NULL REFERENCES tenants(id),\n  gmail_message_id  TEXT NOT NULL,\n  thread_id         TEXT,\n  sender            TEXT NOT NULL,\n  recipients        JSONB NOT NULL DEFAULT '[]',\n  subject           TEXT,\n  body_plain        TEXT,\n  body_html         TEXT,\n  received_at       TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL,\n  attachments       JSONB NOT NULL DEFAULT '[]',\n  labels            JSONB NOT NULL DEFAULT '[]',\n  raw_payload       JSONB,\n  ingested_at       TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT NOW(),\n  updated_at        TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT NOW(),\n\n  CONSTRAINT uq_tenant_gmail_message UNIQUE (tenant_id, gmail_message_id)\n);\n\nCREATE INDEX idx_emails_tenant_id ON emails (tenant_id);\nCREATE INDEX idx_emails_received_at ON emails (tenant_id, received_at DESC);\nCREATE INDEX idx_emails_sender ON emails (tenant_id, sender);\n```\n\n**Notes:**\n- `body_plain` and `body_html` are `TEXT` (unbounded) ‚Äî avoid `VARCHAR(n)` for email bodies\n- `recipients`, `attachments`, and `labels` use `JSONB` to accommodate variable-length arrays without separate join tables\n- `raw_payload` stores the full Gmail API `Message` object for debugging; consider stripping body content from this field to avoid double-storing large content\n- All queries must include `WHERE tenant_id = $1` as the first filter condition\n\n---\n\n## Gmail OAuth & Watch Setup (Per Tenant)\n\nEach tenant must complete a one-time OAuth authorization before their inbox can be monitored.\n\n**Required Gmail API scopes:**\n- `https://www.googleapis.com/auth/gmail.readonly` ‚Äî to fetch message content\n- `https://www.googleapis.com/auth/gmail.modify` ‚Äî only if you need to mark messages read or apply labels\n\n**Watch registration** (call this after OAuth completes, and refresh every 7 days ‚Äî Gmail watch subscriptions expire):\n\n```json\nPOST https://gmail.googleapis.com/gmail/v1/users/me/watch\n{\n  \"topicName\": \"projects/YOUR_PROJECT/topics/gmail-inbound\",\n  \"labelIds\": [\"INBOX\"],\n  \"labelFilterBehavior\": \"INCLUDE\"\n}\n```\n\nStore the returned `historyId` as the tenant's baseline ‚Äî you'll use this to call `history.list` incrementally so you don't re-process old messages.\n\n**Watch renewal:** Store the `expiration` timestamp from the watch response and set up a daily job to renew watches expiring within 24 hours.\n\n---\n\n## Multi-Tenant Support\n\nTenant resolution uses the `:tenantId` URL path parameter combined with a per-tenant API key stored in your database.\n\n**Tenant record should include:**\n- `gmail_oauth_tokens` (encrypted) ‚Äî access token, refresh token, expiry\n- `gmail_watch_history_id` ‚Äî the last processed `historyId` for incremental fetching\n- `gmail_watch_expiration` ‚Äî when the Pub/Sub watch subscription expires\n- `webhook_api_key` ‚Äî the secret appended to the Pub/Sub push URL for secondary auth validation\n\n**Isolation guarantees:**\n- All Gmail API calls use the OAuth tokens belonging to the resolved tenant only\n- The `historyId` cursor is stored per-tenant ‚Äî no shared state\n- All database writes and reads are scoped to `tenant_id`\n- The Pub/Sub topic is shared infrastructure, but tenant identity is resolved from the push URL before any data access occurs\n\n---\n\n## Apps Script Alternative (No-Code Setup)\n\nFor tenants who can't complete OAuth flows or prefer a simpler setup, provide a Google Apps Script template they can deploy themselves:\n\n```javascript\nfunction checkNewEmails() {\n  const webhookUrl = \"https://yourapp.com/webhooks/email/gmail/TENANT_ID\";\n  const apiKey = \"TENANT_API_KEY\";\n  const lastRun = PropertiesService.getScriptProperties()\n                    .getProperty(\"lastRun\") || \"2000/01/01\";\n  \n  const threads = GmailApp.search(`after:${lastRun} in:inbox`);\n  \n  threads.forEach(thread => {\n    thread.getMessages().forEach(msg => {\n      const payload = {\n        messageId: msg.getId(),\n        sender: msg.getFrom(),\n        recipients: msg.getTo(),\n        subject: msg.getSubject(),\n        bodyPlain: msg.getPlainBody(),\n        bodyHtml: msg.getBody(),\n        receivedAt: msg.getDate().toISOString()\n      };\n      \n      UrlFetchApp.fetch(webhookUrl, {\n        method: \"POST\",\n        headers: { \"Content-Type\": \"application/json\", \"X-API-Key\": apiKey },\n        payload: JSON.stringify(payload),\n        muteHttpExceptions: true\n      });\n    });\n  });\n  \n  PropertiesService.getScriptProperties()\n    .setProperty(\"lastRun\", new Date().toLocaleDateString(\"en-US\"));\n}\n```\n\nTenants set a time-based trigger (every 1 minute) in Apps Script. This approach doesn't require Pub/Sub or OAuth on your backend ‚Äî the payload arrives pre-parsed, so your endpoint can skip the Gmail API fetch step and ingest directly. The tradeoff is up to a 1-minute delay and reliance on the tenant keeping their Apps Script project active.\n\n---\n\n## Admin Integrations Page ‚Äî `/admin/integrations`\n\n### Microsoft Gmail / Google Workspace Email Section\n\n**Display prominently at the top:**\n\n```\nYour Webhook URL:\nhttps://yourapp.com/webhooks/email/gmail/[tenant-id]\n\nYour API Key:\n[masked key with copy button]\n```\n\n---\n\n**Setup Option A ‚Äî Full Integration (Recommended)**\n\nStep-by-step guide in the UI:\n\n1. **Enable the Gmail API** in your Google Cloud project at console.cloud.google.com ‚Üí APIs & Services ‚Üí Enable APIs ‚Üí search \"Gmail API\"\n2. **Create a Pub/Sub topic** named `gmail-inbound` in the same project\n3. **Create a push subscription** pointing to your webhook URL with `?token=YOUR_API_KEY` appended\n4. **Grant publish rights** to `gmail-api-push@system.gserviceaccount.com` on your Pub/Sub topic (this is the Google-managed service account Gmail uses)\n5. **Click \"Connect Gmail Account\"** in this UI ‚Äî you'll be redirected through Google OAuth to authorize inbox access\n6. **Watch registration happens automatically** after OAuth completes ‚Äî you'll see a green \"Watching Inbox\" status indicator here once active\n\n---\n\n**Setup Option B ‚Äî Apps Script (Simpler)**\n\n1. Open [script.google.com](https://script.google.com) while signed into the Gmail account you want to monitor\n2. Create a new project and paste the Apps Script template provided below\n3. Replace `TENANT_ID` and `TENANT_API_KEY` with the values shown above\n4. Click **Run** once manually to grant permissions\n5. Go to **Triggers ‚Üí Add Trigger** ‚Üí set `checkNewEmails` to run every 1 minute\n\n---\n\n**Field Mapping Reference (Apps Script option):**\n\n| Your Webhook Field | Apps Script / Gmail Value |\n|---|---|\n| `messageId` | `msg.getId()` |\n| `sender` | `msg.getFrom()` |\n| `recipients` | `msg.getTo()` |\n| `subject` | `msg.getSubject()` |\n| `bodyPlain` | `msg.getPlainBody()` |\n| `bodyHtml` | `msg.getBody()` |\n| `receivedAt` | `msg.getDate().toISOString()` |\n\n---\n\n## Edge Cases\n\n**Duplicate delivery:** The `UNIQUE (tenant_id, gmail_message_id)` constraint is the authoritative deduplication guard. Use an `INSERT ... ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING` pattern and return `200` either way so Pub/Sub doesn't retry.\n\n**Missing fields:** Subject, plain body, and HTML body should all be nullable at the application layer. Emails with no subject (common for automated senders) or no plain text body (HTML-only emails) are valid and should be stored as-is.\n\n**Large bodies:** Gmail messages can theoretically be very large. Impose a configurable size cap (e.g., 5MB) on `body_html` and `body_plain` before storage, truncating with a metadata flag (`body_truncated: true`) so downstream consumers know the content is incomplete rather than silently missing.\n\n**Expired watch subscriptions:** If a tenant's Gmail watch expires and isn't renewed, Pub/Sub stops receiving notifications silently ‚Äî no error is thrown. Show an \"Integration Inactive ‚Äî watch expired\" warning in the UI based on the stored expiration timestamp, and send the tenant an email alert 48 hours before expiry.\n\n**OAuth token refresh:** Access tokens expire every 60 minutes. Always attempt a refresh before making Gmail API calls and update the stored tokens. If a refresh token is revoked (tenant disconnects the app from their Google Account), mark the integration as inactive and alert the tenant.\n\n**historyId gaps:** If your server is down when Pub/Sub delivers a notification, you may miss messages. On reconnection, call `history.list` starting from the last stored `historyId` to backfill any gaps. Cap backfill lookback to 7 days, which is Gmail's history retention window.\n\n**Attachments:** Only store attachment metadata (filename, MIME type, size, Gmail attachment ID) in the database by default. Actual attachment content should be fetched on-demand via the Gmail API using the stored attachment ID, rather than eagerly downloading and storing binary content at ingestion time.",
