.list) \n‚Üí Gmail API (messages.get) ‚Üí Parse & store email\n```\n\n**Parse and extract from Gmail API response:**\n- `from` header ‚Üí sender address\n- `to`, `cc`, `bcc` headers ‚Üí recipients\n- `subject` header ‚Üí subject\n- `body.data` (text/plain part) ‚Üí plain text body\n- `body.data` (text/html part) ‚Üí HTML body\n- `internalDate` ‚Üí received timestamp\n- `id` ‚Üí Gmail message ID (used for deduplication)\n- `threadId` ‚Üí conversation thread reference\n- `payload.parts` where `filename` is non-empty ‚Üí attachment metadata (name, MIME type, size, attachment ID)\n\n**HTTP responses:**\n- `200` ‚Äî success or duplicate (Pub/Sub will not retry on 200)\n- `400` ‚Äî payload malformed or tenant resolution failed\n- `401` ‚Äî auth token invalid\n- `500` ‚Äî internal error (Pub/Sub **will** retry, so only use this when a retry is appropriate)\n\n> **Critical:** Return `200` for duplicates and known-bad messages you've already handled. Returning non-2xx causes Pub/Sub to retry with exponential backoff for up to 7 days.\n\n---\n\n## Database\n\n```sql\nCREATE TABLE emails (\n  id                UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),\n  tenant_id         UUID NOT NULL REFERENCES tenants(id),\n  gmail_message_id  TEXT NOT NULL,\n  thread_id         TEXT,\n  sender            TEXT NOT NULL,\n  recipients        JSONB NOT NULL DEFAULT '[]',\n  subject           TEXT,\n  body_plain        TEXT,\n  body_html         TEXT,\n  received_at       TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL,\n  attachments       JSONB NOT NULL DEFAULT '[]',\n  labels            JSONB NOT NULL DEFAULT '[]',\n  raw_payload       JSONB,\n  ingested_at       TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT NOW(),\n  updated_at        TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT NOW(),\n\n  CONSTRAINT uq_tenant_gmail_message UNIQUE (tenant_id, gmail_message_id)\n);\n\nCREATE INDEX idx_emails_tenant_id ON emails (tenant_id);\nCREATE INDEX idx_emails_received_at ON emails (tenant_id, received_at DESC);\nCREATE INDEX idx_emails_sender ON emails (ten