b push URL for secondary auth validation\n\n**Isolation guarantees:**\n- All Gmail API calls use the OAuth tokens belonging to the resolved tenant only\n- The `historyId` cursor is stored per-tenant ‚Äî no shared state\n- All database writes and reads are scoped to `tenant_id`\n- The Pub/Sub topic is shared infrastructure, but tenant identity is resolved from the push URL before any data access occurs\n\n---\n\n## Apps Script Alternative (No-Code Setup)\n\nFor tenants who can't complete OAuth flows or prefer a simpler setup, provide a Google Apps Script template they can deploy themselves:\n\n```javascript\nfunction checkNewEmails() {\n  const webhookUrl = \"https://yourapp.com/webhooks/email/gmail/TENANT_ID\";\n  const apiKey = \"TENANT_API_KEY\";\n  const lastRun = PropertiesService.getScriptProperties()\n                    .getProperty(\"lastRun\") || \"2000/01/01\";\n  \n  const threads = GmailApp.search(`after:${lastRun} in:inbox`);\n  \n  threads.forEach(thread => {\n    thread.getMessages().forEach(msg => {\n      const payload = {\n        messageId: msg.getId(),\n        sender: msg.getFrom(),\n        recipients: msg.getTo(),\n        subject: msg.getSubject(),\n        bodyPlain: msg.getPlainBody(),\n        bodyHtml: msg.getBody(),\n        receivedAt: msg.getDate().toISOString()\n      };\n      \n      UrlFetchApp.fetch(webhookUrl, {\n        method: \"POST\",\n        headers: { \"Content-Type\": \"application/json\", \"X-API-Key\": apiKey },\n        payload: JSON.stringify(payload),\n        muteHttpExceptions: true\n      });\n    });\n  });\n  \n  PropertiesService.getScriptProperties()\n    .setProperty(\"lastRun\", new Date().toLocaleDateString(\"en-US\"));\n}\n```\n\nTenants set a time-based trigger (every 1 minute) in Apps Script. This approach doesn't require Pub/Sub or OAuth on your backend ‚Äî the payload arrives pre-parsed, so your endpoint can skip the Gmail API fetch step and ingest directly. The tradeoff is up to a 1-minute delay and reliance on the tenant keeping their Apps Script project active.\n\n---\n\n## Admin Integrations Page ‚Äî `/admin/integrations`\n\n### Microsoft Gmail / Google Workspace Email Section\n\n**Display prominently at the top:**\n\n```\nYour Webhook URL:\nhttps://yourapp.com/webhooks/email/gmail/[tenant-id]\n\nYour API Key:\n[masked key with copy button]\n```\n\n---\n\n**Setup Option A ‚Äî Full Integration (Recommended)**\n\nStep-by-step guide in the UI:\n\n1. **Enable the Gmail API** in your Google Cloud project at console.cloud.google.com ‚Üí APIs & Services ‚Üí Enable APIs ‚Üí search \"Gmail API\"\n2. **Create a Pub/Sub topic** named `gmail-inbound` in the same project\n3. **Create a push subscription** pointing to your webhook URL with `?token=YOUR_API_KEY` appended\n4. **Grant publish rights** to `gmail-api-push@system.gserviceaccount.com` on your Pub/Sub topic (this is the Google-managed service account Gmail uses)\n5. **Click \"Connect Gmail Account\"** in this UI ‚Äî you'll be redirected through Google OAuth to authorize inbox access\n6. **Watch registration happens automatically** after OAuth completes ‚Äî you'll see a green \"Watching Inbox\" status indicator here once active\n\n---\n\n**Setup Option B ‚Äî Apps Script (Simpler)**\n\n1. Open [script.google.com](https://script.google.com) while signed into the Gmail account you want to monitor\n2. Create a new project and paste the Apps Script template provided below\n3. Replace `TENANT_ID` and `TENANT_API_KEY` with the values shown above\n4. Click **Run** once manually to grant permissions\n5. Go to **Triggers ‚Üí Add Trigger** ‚Üí set `checkNewEmails` to run every 1 minute\n\n---\n\n**Field Mapping Reference (Apps Script option):**\n\n| Your Webhook Field | Apps Script / Gmail Value |\n|---|---|\n| `messageId` | `msg.getId()` |\n| `sender` | `msg.getFrom()` |\n| `recipients` | `msg.getTo()` |\n| `subject` | `msg.getSubject()` |\n| `bodyPlain` | `msg.getPlainBody()` |\n| `bodyHtml` | `msg.getBody()` |\n| `received